### IT-05: Concurrent Tool\_Use Blocks — Thread Safety

| Field | Value |
| --- | --- |
| **ID** | IT-05 |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Type** | Integration Test |
| **Requirement** | NFR Concurrency, TC-9 |
| **File** | kiro-rs/src/anthropic/tests/handlers\_test.rs |
| **Preconditions** | Tokio multi-threaded runtime |

**Test Steps:**

| Step | Action | Expected Result |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Create shared Arc<Mutex<ConversationHistory>> | Shared history |
| 2 | Spawn 10 concurrent tokio tasks, each storing a unique tool\_use\_id | Concurrent writes |
| 3 | Wait for all tasks to complete | No panics, no deadlocks |
| 4 | Verify all 10 IDs are in history via get\_all\_tool\_use\_ids() | All 10 present |
| 5 | Verify each ID retrievable via find\_tool\_use() | All found |

**Test Data:** IDs: tooluse\_CONC\_0 through tooluse\_CONC\_9

