## 6. Appendix

### Test Data Setup

All test data is defined inline in test fixtures. No external database or seed scripts required — kiro-rs uses in-memory conversation history only.

**Fixture Files Location:** kiro-rs/tests/fixtures/

| File | Description |
| --- | --- |
| tool\_use\_response.json | Single tool\_use response from API |
| multi\_tool\_response.json | Response with 3 tool\_use blocks |
| text\_response.json | Plain text response (no tools) |
| empty\_id\_response.json | Malformed response with empty ID |
| missing\_id\_response.json | Malformed response without id field |

### Environment Configuration

# Test configuration (Cargo.toml)
[dev-dependencies]
proptest = "1.0"
wiremock = "0.5"
tokio-test = "0.4"
tracing-test = "0.2"
reqwest = { version = "0.11", features = ["json"] }

